My YouTube Video Survey Report

Plot One

This bar plot shows how many YouTube videos I watched per genre. I was interested in creating this plot because I wished to use it to find out which genres of video I watch the most. From the bar plot, I am able to see the five genres with the most videos watched, in descending order, and how many videos I have watched for each of these genres.

Plot Two

This box plot shows a comparison between the length of the YouTube videos that I watched, for whether I am subscribed to the channel or not. I created this plot because I wanted to see if there were any trends in the length of YouTube videos I watch, and if I only tend to watch longer videos if I am subscribed to them. The box plot also includes green arrows, which show the average length of YouTube videos watched.

Plot Three

This bar plot shows how many YouTube videos of each genre that I watched per month. I decided to create this plot because the two months represent the videos watched for the two projects relating to this survey. This means that I can see if there are any correlations between whether I watched more videos of a certain genre during one project versus the other.
